    public class InitialWeightRankSearch
extends RankSearch
    RankSearch over the initial weights and then run weight learning like normal. TODO(eriq): It would be great if we could construct the internal WLA on our side instead of relying on it to be passed in (we have to ensure that the caller uses the same rules and DBs).

      • inspectLocation

        protected double inspectLocation(double[] weights)
        Description copied from class: BaseGridSearch
        Inspect the location defined by the given weights and give back its score (lower is better). This method may modify weights if it wants to store a different set of weights than those initially passed in. The rules have already been set with the given weights, they are only passed in so the method has a chance to modify them before the result is stored. This is a prime method for child classes to override. Implementers should make sure to correct (negate) the value that comes back from the Evaluator if lower is better for that evaluator.
        Overrides:
        inspectLocation in class BaseGridSearch
